According to National Daily report, an Anambra lawmaker representing the Aguata North constituency, the same community as the governor of the state, Prof. Chukwuma Chukwuma Soludo was kidnapped last week and has been confirmed dead as he was beheaded by unknown gunmen suspected to be members of the Indigenous People of Biafra/IPOB.
The lawmaker whose head was mounted at Chisco park in the Amichi community, after a viral video which appeared online in which their freshly beheaded head was seen placed on a carton by the roadside along with a handwritten note placed by the side.
The governor of the state has, however, condemned the act and has urged security agencies to find those responsible for the death of the lawmaker, and reacting to the sad news, popular activist, Adeyanju Deji took to his verified Facebook page saying the beheading of the lawmaker is barbaric and stands condemned while urging security agencies should find those responsible as he initiated that they know who the criminals are and where they are.



